    "recap_headline": "Abilene Christian",
    "recap_text": "ABILENE -\nDesignated hitter\nDiego Cardenas\nheadlined a terrific day at the plate for ACU as the Wildcats took down Loyola Marymount 11-5 in the second of a three-game series Saturday afternoon at Bullock Brothers Ballpark at Crutcher Scott Field.\nCardenas went 3/4 with six RBI, including a three-run home run in the sixth and a solo bomb in the eighth. All nine Wildcats in the lineup recorded at least one hit with J.T. Thompson and\nGavin Brzozowski\nturning in two-hit games.\nGrant Watkins\n, hitting leadoff, doubled to left field in the first inning and later scored on\nRyan Jones'\ngroundout, giving ACU the 1-0 lead.\nIn the fifth inning,\nNick Arias\nwalked and later scored on Jones' RBI double. Cardenas' three-run homer extended the lead, and then\nGavin Brzozowski\nadded another run with an RBI single, scoring\nJT Thompson\nto put the Wildcats in front 7-0.\nCardenas contributed further in the sixth with a two-run single to center, bringing in Arias and Watkins.\nKanon Sundgren\nrecorded his first 2-RBI game of hte season when he slapped an RBI single in the seventh.\nIn the eighth, the Lions capitalized on several walks and a sacrifice fly to score three runs, but Cardenas added the solo homer to center to keep them at bay.\nAidan Coleman\ndelivered a strong performance for the Wildcats, pitching five innings without allowing a run and striking out two batters while conceding five hits. He posted a season-high total of 82 pitches in this outing.\nNoah Galvan\nand\nDavid Jeon\ncollectively held the opposition scoreless in their relief stints, with Galvan pitching 1 2/3 innings without allowing a hit, despite issuing three walks, and Jeon securing the final out with a single pitch.\nFreshman\nBrady Ladusau\nalso showcased his speed with two stolen bases while also drawing a season-high total of three walks.\nUP NEXT\nThe series concludes on Sunday with a 12 p.m. first pitch at Bullock Brothers Ballpark for Rally Cats Day.\nIn a separate schedule update, ACU's home game against UIW on Wednesday, March 18 has been moved up to a 4 p.m. start."
  },
